##On the Wuhan Front Line, he became the coolest Knight

WMSYGSDR

Functional introduction, each line has a serious person, even ordinary people have extraordinary stories. Huazhong University of Science and Technology Press Official non-fiction story platform, the story of the people will meet here.

Today, the government has introduced a variety of measures to address the travel difficulties of health care workers, but there are still individual needs that can not be met. Gao said he would hold out until the day the traffic problems of the medical staff were eased.

”

On January 23,2020, the headquarters of the prevention and control of pneumonia in Wuhan COVID-19 issued a public announcement. From 10:00 on January 23, the city bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger services in Wuhan were suspended, airports and railway stations are temporarily closed from the Han corridor.

This is a necessary measure to control the epidemic. But it also poses a challenge for those who need to travel every day, especially those on the front lines.

At 2:12 p.m. on January 24, when Gao Yu, a Wuhan resident, discovered the problem, he did not hesitate, immediately in the friend circle posted a message: "There are voluntary free for medical personnel to provide vehicle transport services, speed contact me. ". There is a high risk of infection, please consider. If you don't, give it to someone who does. I wechat phone synchronization, for help. Gao Yu: * * * * . I dare any of you to come with me."

The most special Spring Festival of his life began..

On New Year's Eve, become a knight

Gao Yu, born in 1975, is a manager of a 4s shop in Wuhan. On January 24, after seeing the traffic paralysis, many medical staff went to work for more than eight hours, but they could not go home in time to rest after work. Some even had to walk for more than an hour to go to and from work. He could not sit still and decided to go into the battle.

At the time, Wuhan's volunteer motorcade set up three wechat groups, divided into Wuchang, Hankou and Hanyang regions. The Koos were in Hankou, so they went into the Hankou. Not long after entering the group, Gao Yu received the first demand, take Hubei Province Third People's Hospital an emergency department nurse to go home from work.

He puts on a mask, a raincoat, gloves and a hood, sets up his goggles, and fires up his ireser 7, a festive red, which he has been driving for three years without a problem. The car turned into a rally car, has already finished disinfection, drove out of the community, into the gloomy Wuhan Street.

At the hospital, he opened the window and blew away the virus. After the first one, I didn't dare to go home, so I just sat in the car. All of a sudden, wechat Ding Dong a ring, it was just the emergency doctor gave him a 30 yuan Hongbao. But Gao Yu refused, "I am the obligation to pick up HA. "

Then he started his way back to his home in Hankou Railway Station, about to pull over. At 3:30, the call came from a traffic cop friend of his. The voice on the other end of the WECHAT video is anxious, "Gao Yu, I was on duty on a nearby road when a doctor who was returning from a trip to Wuhan got out of the Hankou Railway Station and stopped at the side of the road for an hour. I asked the boss, I wanted to send him, but the boss didn't approve. I just saw your circle of friends picking you up and dropping you off. Can you come pick me up and drop me off?"

Gao Yu quickly turned the Ireser 7 around and found the place where his friend and doctor were waiting. Wang Qiang, getting into the car, was a little tired, also a little anxious: "thank you, I went to Caidian People's Hospital. " Gao Yu chatted with him: "where is home? "? How much fever is there in the hospital?"Wang Qiang said to Gao Yu."I'm from CAIDIAN People's Hospital. Originally prepared to have dinner in his hometown in Hefei, did not expect to have received the news of the construction of the Fire Mountain in the afternoon, so immediately rushed back to Wuhan. "Just as we, Caidian District, are pulling out our forces, the CAIDIAN People's Hospital is likely to be the focus of the pulling out... "

New Year's Eve, the streets don't seem to smell at all. From Hankou Railway Station to Caidian People's Hospital, it was quiet for thirty kilometers. Outside, the road was flat and there was no need to worry about the traffic jam.

Forty minutes later, the car stopped, and Wang Qiang thanked him. Gao Yu exclaims: "This doctor is quite not easy, finally New Year's Eve can not eat at home, have to rush to the hospital to treat patients, too great. " After that, two people no longer contact. Did the doctor ever go to Vulcan Mountain? Gao Yu also does not know, "drive a person is my business, other, how do I know? "

At 5:12 p.m. , Gao Yu rushed back to Hankou from Caidian District and picked up the third doctor to return to his home on long harbor road. The doctor told Gao Yu that he wore an N95 mask for a week. Because different departments have different amounts of protection resources are insufficient, they are more dangerous, only to fight their own resistance. Listen, Gao Yu this big old man, while driving, shed tears.

He then took paramedics twice more, across the Kong Hon, the riverbank, Hanyang, Wuchang and Caidian District. By the time the last passenger of the day was delivered, it was after 6:00 p.m. He gassed up his eraser 7, but didn't know where to go next.

As the outbreak began to be confirmed, the city was gearing up for battle, and the air was filled with panic and tension. The Spring Festival did not have the atmosphere of previous years. Gao was worried about the risk of infection and didn't want his family to know what he was doing. On the evening of New Year's Eve, Gao Yu decided not to go home for New Year's Eve dinner. Since he wouldn't be home for dinner anyway, his parents wouldn't suspect that being alone was easy.

He was moved when his friend, Captain Fu Yong of the Kong Hon Traffic Brigade, learned that he had not come home for New Year's Eve dinner and cooked dumplings for him.

At 7:45 p.m. , he received a list from a female nurse, "leaving tomorrow at 7:00 and going to work at about 8:00. " Gao replied, "pick up on time. "

Empty streets, no fireworks, no drums and gongs, very quiet night, back home, after 12 o'clock, in the lunar year, he was 45 years old.

2. City Lights, retrograde together

Early on the morning of January 25, Gao Yu upgraded his protective gear and replaced his hat with a motorcycle helmet.

At 6:51, he arrived at the rendezvous ahead of schedule, driving a double flash to await medical attention. After being sent to the Central Hospital, the medical staff must send a mask to Gao Yu. Gao Yu, don't. Instead, she threw it in Gowoo's car.

Then he got a call from a mother and daughter. Her mother is in Tongji, and her daughter works in the Fourth Hospital of Gutian road. They had been walking for almost an hour before they reached Gao Yu. All the empty taxis along the way, when they heard they were going to the hospital, wouldn't pick them up. Gao Yu delivered them one after the other.

At 9:35 pm, after delivering the last of the doctors, he had the audacity to let his friend drop off a bowl of noodles. When the car is about to arrive, he told friends: "I do not go into the community, you put the noodles on the hood of my car, do not talk to me, something Wechat said... " rivers and lakes at night, lights dim, he ate the bowl of "best" noodles, not left.

On the morning of January 26, a nurse in the group called for a taxi last night. She was going from the second road in Gutian to the Zhongfa Hospital in Caidian.

GOWOO picked her up. On the bus, the nurse Yuan Lingchun regrets, after the city, no bus, a person to go to work to go three and a half hours, and her unit a colleague, is to go four hours to work.

"It's too far away, " said Gao Yu. "But you have to go. If you don't, people won't get off work. I'll take over. "

Gao Yu was silent.

After delivery, Gaoyu said: "If you work inconvenient, can call me in the group. " That night, gaoyu escort Yuan Lingchun home. Originally, she is Tongji Hospital, this day in the Chinese and French hospital to participate in training.

As time went on, Gao Yu found the pain point of the medical staff. In order to solve the problem of medical staff commuting to and from work, the hospital has set up a regular shuttle bus. However, there is only one trip to and from work, the lines and stops are fixed. If you want to catch the bus, medical staff will have to walk to the rendezvous, some will be far from home, even seven or eight kilometers. Moreover, the work is a unified time point, Gao Yu can only receive one or two, the work is very difficult to agree. However, the time off work is more flexible, he can take a few people back, as long as the other side is willing to wait.

Go out every day, Gao Yu will be in the car to reserve some yogurt, snacks, bread, etc. , hungry, eat a little. When he got home in the evening, his mother cooked a hot dinner. After the meal, he began to deal with the news in the group.

The original group is sub-regional, gaoyu found this across the three towns of Wuhan medical staff to work adverse, so he simply built a group, regardless of the region far and near, unconditional pick-up. Soon, the large group full, for the convenience of management, and divided into two small groups. One's a paramedic, the other's a driver. In this way, he realized the need for medical care and volunteer drivers one by one docking. It didn't take long for the medical staff to reach over 300 people.

On February 4, at 8:06 a.m. , he saw the news that a young male doctor, Liu Yu, had been unable to get a taxi from his sister-in-law in Hankou to the Wuchang Provincial Women's and children's Hospital. At that time, he had just delivered another doctor, found that the group has information, quickly contact each other. "I sent a group message and waited for a long time. Seeing that I had no one to take me, I had already ridden a mobike, got on the Second Ring Road and was ready to cross the river by bike, " Liu said. Gao asked him to turn on his seat-sharing and immediately drove to the second ring road to rescue him. At 8:16, on the Second Ring Road, he received Liu Yu. Liu Yu put mobike on the side of the road, sat down in the back seat and rushed to the hospital.

At 9:30 pm, Gao Yu received a special medical staff who had just finished the night shift at Wuhan Eleven Hospital. "paying tribute to the doctor from Kwong Yuen Estate, who has applied to support Wuhan, she said that the people of Wuhan had supported Wenchuan County before and that she should repay them. "

In addition to transport medical staff, his business also send protective clothing, medical equipment, almost everything..

3. The "old stick" principle in Hankou

This is not Gao Yu's first charity event.

Gao Yu is a veteran of Hankou. He is 45 years old. He loved photography, from the beginning of the wedding, to enter the professional circle, has been ten years. However, he is more love is off-road vehicle and motorcycle, in Wuhan's off-road and Motorcycle Club, little known.

"Laogan" , a term coined by Wuhan's hooligans, refers to the middle-aged men of Hankou's indigenous people. Gao Yu face appears old, "many friends, loyalty, have face" , can be called old pole. Wuhan folklorist GE Liang said, than "old pole" a little younger is "bamboo pole" , and then old can be called "old Miaopi" "old Huopi. Some people say that the "old pole" in Wuhan is more pragmatic than the "old KLA" in Mordor, less conventional than the "Pao ge" in foggy metropolis, and more convinced of the truth of life than the "old cannon" in Didu. Something like that.

Gao Yu was born in the Gaozhi family of Laohankou, with an older sister, who had married. Mother is an old doctor, Jilin people, has in the PLA field hospital, Zhongshan Hospital and other work. His father was a senior construction engineer from Wuhan. As a family member of the doctor, he felt a duty to himself.

In the eyes of his friends, he is quite chivalrous. In the summer of 2016, Gao Yu's car friend and lover accidentally overturned on the road and fell into the undergrowth of the cliff. At that time, he was working in Wuhan, saw the news, immediately rushed from Wuhan to Dawu Niangniang Mountain. Arrived at the scene, several fire officers and soldiers will be friends of the car lover with a stretcher to carry up, will be exhausted. There were a lot of people around, but there was nothing to do but wait. Without a word, Gao Yu shouted "let me come" . He tied a rope around his body and hurried down. He and three other fire officers and soldiers, will be injured in the car with friends up, so that the fracture area can be sent to the hospital in time to help.

In the summer of 2017, Lake Townsend was flooded during the rainy season in Wuhan. One evening, playing in the group of cars, a car friend home emergency help, his home in the Wuhan suburb of Xinzhou Phoenix town, flood affected town life. Gao Yu saw, immediately with a few friends together call for donations, the next morning, rushed to the supermarket to buy food and supplies. A line of people, more than a dozen cars drove past, solved the immediate crisis of the disaster area.

As a "old club" , because of straightforward personality, like to open mouth on the troll, his friends sent him a nickname "troll brother. In September 2019, Wuhan issued a "Most strictly prohibited motorcycle ban" , expanding the scope of motorcycle ban, banned motorcycles into the third ring road... . However, soon after, a 41-pair Blessing ceremony of the Unification Church was held on the bosom friend, with dozens of motorcycles on board the cruise ship. "This is not explicitly prohibited, but in public violation? The face of publicity? " Gao Yukai believes that the bosom friend is within a ring, and marriage is not an emergency official business. After this spurt, many netizens support him, and for a few days, he suddenly became an Internet celebrity.

After the city, to join the relief of work difficulties of the medical volunteers ranks, he is not empty filled with blood, but has its own "capital. ".

In 2007, he concentrated on exercise for half a year, has been very healthy, in his words, "a good foundation. ". His wechat profile pictures are pictures of him with a motorcycle, a crew cut, sharp and firm eyes, Crisp White T-shirt, sitting on the grass, behind the stocky motorcycle. Usually, he likes to ride long-distance motorcycle journey with the motorcycle friends, the high speed 800 kilometers, the national highway 500 kilometers, he has run. "people who have been on motorbikes for a long time are much more comfortable in their cars. There is no comparison! " He said in a subdued tone.

For the first week, Gao could only sleep three hours a day, leaving the house at five or six o'clock, and then going to bed at three o'clock in the morning. He came home late, had to deal with the news in the group, rarely slept during the day, to the third day of medical transport, not too energetic. Two of the 20-odd days of transport, he got sleepy at 12:00 noon, he called the paramedics, "excuse me, you find someone else, I need to rest. " Then, he was in the car for half an hour, to continue into the fight. At the most, Gao shuttled more than 20 medical staff a day.

Not Every volunteer has his strong physique, and not every volunteer has a selfless heart.

Over time, Gao found that some volunteers did not want to take the call from the community service center, while others had conditions and charged no fees. In addition, "far away, early, late, small hospitals, men do not take the call. " And his principle is "no matter how far, as long as I wait, I will go. ".

Gao Remembers that the longest list he received, running 70 kilometers, was from the western end of Wuhan East West Lake 13 branch ditch, to Zuoling 120 medical emergency station. This 120-year-old nurse, she works a couple of shifts, two nights, three days off.

Gao's gesture has touched many doctors, some of whom bring him breakfast, beef noodles or hot-dry noodles or Churros, some of whom send him a mask or a carton of milk to remind him to take care of himself. Several nurses had given him private red envelopes, but Gao rejected them all. "I'm just doing my part, " he told them. "I don't want you walking to and from work. I don't want you riding your bikes. "

After each ride, he disinfects the car with a 75 percent alcohol spray bottle, then leaves the door open to air for about 30 minutes before picking up another fare.

From morning till 9:30 in the evening, my mother had already heated up the meal. Before entering, Gao Yu takes off the protective clothing, the mask takes off the processing disinfection. For Safety, he has been isolating himself from his family these days.

4. I'm not a hero or a saint

"You built a platform for 300 people? I built three wechat groups are thousands of people, I and you have what good planning, you are to make money, say so nice to do? Your platform is good to use you, the platform is good again, does the person need not drive a car to send? On the platform? Will your platform be ready to leave at 3:30?"February 5th, gao Yu ruthlessly scorned a platform promoter who invited him to join.

At first, he asked a few female volunteers to help him with the group's work so that he could dock the staff's car more quickly. When he gets home at night, he's GonNa take over. However, because the work is tedious and so on, the volunteer withdraws one after another, only then Gao Yu manages all by himself. He has his own criteria: 1. Issue a work license photo (or other document photo) . 2. Take a picture with him in the car. I can't do both. I'm sorry. Please find another car.

On Feb. 4, Gao received a nurse, who boarded the bus and asked for a group photo. The nurse kept her head down. Please keep it up. Why, she asked, do I have to look up? Gao Yu said he didn't want to say I was taking pictures. Then she looked up and out of the window. Then, Gao Yu told her to get out of the car. She asked, why? Ko woo-do, I'm tired. How am I supposed to get home without a car? Gao Yu said, how should I know. Then he deleted the photo in front of her, and she asked him to delete her wechat account and check his phone's photo album. Gao Yu will do as you say. Then she got out of the car.

In this regard, Gao Yu has his own reasons, "I'm not a hero, I'm not a saint, I just do what I have to do. I do this on my own, I have a process, and I don't need an explanation. Why do we have to take a group photo? If it's acceptable, we'll give it to them. If it's not acceptable, we'll figure it out. People who know me know I have a bad temper, so don't think I'm nice and I don't care what other people think."

5. An epidemic, the world

On Feb. 3, He Hui, one of the volunteers, died of a new pneumonia. Some of the volunteers were very sad. In fact, in the face of the new coronavirus epidemic, then the first batch of volunteers, to be able to adhere to the less, the new volunteers also in the wave.

Gao Yu expressed regret over the death of He Hui, "He could have been infected before. He only ran the car for two or three days. Many people asked me why I was not afraid of new pneumonia, in fact, I would like to say: I have no heart and lungs, no lung, with what infection? Of course not."The volunteers are more independent of each other, take each list, not as a whole, but in the same way.

For the community, Gao Yu is not only understand the difficulties of its small number of reasons, but also hate iron into steel. The government issued a document requesting the community to give priority to sending and receiving medical personnel. As a result, many communities were unable to send and receive medical personnel. Some not only did not send, but also gave Gao Yu's phone directly to the medical staff. Gao Yu find each other theory, the original because of the fear of infection, the driver of the company does not allow to send to the community driver pick up and send medical staff. At the same time, also take photos and video propaganda in the community to send and receive medical staff..

Gao Yu was indignant, "I take the money and I don't work and I want compliments, and then we stupid drivers from non-corporate platforms pick me up and give my phone number to the paramedics. The funniest thing is, a community in Hanyang has its own car arrangement, the community staff contact me, a living in Kong Hon, want me to help transport, I see in the medical workers manufacturing industry, sent, or sent from Hanyang to Panlongcheng. These things, community cadres are a bit helpless, community pressure, root in those who took money in the various vehicles platform, platform to make money, but also want to take the opportunity to show his face advertising."

It was not the only time Gao Yu had lost heart.

On the night of February 4, he was approached by a nurse to negotiate a price because his wife wanted to save a little money on gas. He was angry, "I get up early and stay up late. I don't eat or sleep? To be a hero? For a thank you? To trick the paramedics into taking a picture with a mask on? I'm risking my life, including my parents'! You don't want to drive your wife to your own car. You want to save money? In fact, I sent so many days, I have seen, which is not cheap neighborhood, but if married, the family must have a car, even if some families have special circumstances, but there is no car waiting for us to send free of charge must also. But I don't want to say, I still can send send, install a Tiao (Wuhan dialect, fool) ."

So he started spending more time with each person to make sure that they really needed the car.

On February 5th, a Good Samaritan reminded him, "brother Gaoyu, the epidemic in Wuhan is more serious than we thought. The doctor you sent last time was infected on February 1, and the hospital beds are in short supply at present. They are all taking medicine and quarantining at home. You must arouse attention and pay attention to protection! " He took a Selfie and posted it on his facebook page. "In case I die, you can see the last of me. "

On This Day, his community posted a public number, "our community now have fever patients 5 cases, have sent away one, these six cases are... " gaoyu looked, fortunately, there is no unit where he is.

6. Valentine's Day without Valentines

As early as noon on January 25, when I learned that Gao Yu had been sent to the hospital, Gao Yu's mother expressed strong opposition, "What are you going to do? Staying at home is the best way to fight the virus. Don't be kind and help, just listen to my mother who has been a doctor all her life! " Gao replied: "I'm fine. I have good resistance. "

Later, looking at the stubborn gaoyu unchanged, gaoyu mother has no way, can not stop, also let him go.

In fact, before taking part in the transportation of medical personnel, he prepared for the worst: "I just do it with the mindset that I'm going to be infected, which means if I end up infected, but I'm not going to die, I can be cured, so I'm not afraid. "

On the afternoon of February 6, when his mother caught a cold and there was no one at home to take care of the cooking, Gao had to stop the car. He cooks, he takes care of his mother. He self-mockery, "a good car, pull a good skin, under a good side. "

On the 12th, mother recovered from a cold. After a five-day absence, seeing the volunteer convoy begin to dwindle, he decides to drive the wrong way again and return the king. "Guys, hold on for two days. There are fewer and fewer cars these days. Thank you for your hard work. I'll be right back. "

On This Day, Gao Yu met a "breach of contract" of medical staff. He received a taxi from Fang Ling, a nurse at Yaxin Hospital, around 2:00 p.m. and left for his home at Qili Temple in Hanyang. As a result, Gao arrived early after delivering the last nurse. By six o'clock, Fang Ling wasn't answering her phone or her wechat account. By 7:40, another nurse called for a cab, and he had to apologize. "I have to go, can't let the next one also wait. " Later, Fang Ling contacted him, said sorry to him, just been working overtime. Gao Yu jokes, "just stood me up, and now I go from Qiaokou District to pick her up. Abuse me a thousand times, like first love. "

In the early hours of February 14th, in a departure from the usual romantic scenes of flowers, wine and dinner, couples in the same room snuggled up to each other during the outbreak, lovers in the same city who can't see each other (even the quarantined ones) start "cloud dating" by phone and video. Gao Yu, 45, still lives a single life. He has had inappropriate love, but "because of poor" and will be dedicated to the motorcycle and car, can not afford to buy a house, has not entered the marriage.

"The first thing to do on Valentine's Day is to arrange the stamp of a pass to donate a car to Pujiang County (Sichuan) , " he said. "It's another Valentine's Day without a Valentine. "

I got up at 4:50 and left at 5:15. It was still dark. At 5:29, he picked up one at Liberation Avenue, where he had to wait for two more paramedics. At 5:54, he was taken to a hospital in Wuhan. 6:13, Hanyang Hospital.

He wrapped his head in a black hood and put on a hat, half a white mask sticking out except for his eyes and a small forehead, a bit like the Dark Knight in the Christopher Nolan Movie.

Later, in an air raid to transport medical personnel, he also found time to stamp the passes of the drivers of the Kong Hon Brigade's donated convoy to Pujiang County (Sichuan) , and took the convoy to the Daihuang expressway entrance and watched as the convoy of vehicles carrying relief supplies pulled out, one of the frontline officers paid a silent tribute to all the compatriots who had assisted Wuhan.

On this day, his path spread across a number of hospitals in Wuhan, there is a hospital, Hanyang Hospital, children's Hospital, Zhongshan Hospital, Tongji Hospital, Wuhan Bauhinia Hospital, four hospitals, six hospitals, and more than a dozen medical and nursing staff.

At 6 p.m. , the National Meteorological Centre issued a blue alert for snowstorms: Heavy snow is expected in central and eastern Liaoning, southeastern Jilin, northeastern Shandong, northeastern and western Hubei, and the Dabie Mountains in Anhui from 2000 to 2000 on February 14.

As the night deepens, the wind begins to howl outside, and lightning and thunder seem to crack open the heavens and the earth. "I finished my work well today, " Gao concluded. "I won't get up until one o'clock tomorrow morning to get out of the car. I don't believe in Guan Xuan's 24-hour standing by. I only believe in myself. I never stand by. I just go. "

Early on the morning of February 15, Wuhan City, Snow was flying, the world is one of the new, slippery roads, driving extra careful.

At 12:03 p.m. , Gao received a female nurse in Changhongqiao, Nanhu, Wuchang District. "She commutes to work by bicycle every day for an hour and a half. It's snowing today and she can't cycle. " twenty-two minutes later, he arrived at the Renshou Road Community Health Service Station. Here, Gao Yu has transported a dozen people.

Major platforms are serving health care workers, but they do not cover the entire population, Gao said. For example, Didi, the largest ride-hailing platform, has 500 places for medical transport in large hospitals such as Tongji Xiehe, and 200 places in general hospitals. The community health service stations belong to the "No care zone" , not only do they have no places, the volunteers aren't too keen either.

It was still snowing at night. Gao is still on his way. On the empty streets, high-rise buildings on both sides of Wuhan Avenue Glow with blood-red lights that say "Wuhan will win" and "China will win" in yellow letters.

On the night of February 15th, it was snowing. At 9:45, he was in the group@all the people, "tomorrow morning at 6:20 Sharp at Wusheng road four hospitals in front of the car, too late, please reply. " Soon, there are four medical staff in the group replied "Yes" one after another. Gao Yu self-mockery, "abruptly from a black taxi to play a black bus. "

On the morning of February 16, Gao Yu received Yuan Lingchun again today. Gao Yu asked: "change the place? " Yuan Lingchun said: "I am Tongji headquarters, the last time is to go to the Chinese and French hospital there to participate in training. This back to the headquarters, the distance on a little bit closer! Hard you! "

Today, the government has introduced a variety of measures to address the travel difficulties of health care workers, but there are still individual needs that can not be met. Gao said he would hold out until the day the traffic problems of the medical staff were eased.

In Wuhan Today, Gao Yu is just one of many ordinary people who have made silent contributions to the fight against the epidemic. Around him, such as the private car driver to pick up and take care of the medical staff of no less than 200 people, including more than 10 in his influence, joined the ranks of volunteers. They said, "big brother, I want to be like you. "

All names except Gao Yu
